  "notes": "Shawiya (Tacawit), a Zenati Berber language of the Aurès. Written here in the Northern-Berber Latin alphabet (the same convention as Kabyle: ⟨c⟩ = /ʃ/, ⟨ɣ⟩, ⟨x⟩ = /χ/, ⟨ɛ⟩ = /ʕ/, dot-under letters = emphatics). Tifinagh and Arabic-script spellings also exist and are NOT modelled here. Spirantisation is pervasive: /t d b k ɡ/ surface as [θ ð β ç ʝ] outside tense/geminate positions, which is captured in the allophone map."
}
